---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout>
	<main>
		<h1>Sanjay Srikanth</h1>
		<section class="bio">
		<p>
		I am a <span id="age"></span>-year-old software engineer based in Santa Barbara, California, United States.
		</p>
		<p>
		I grew up in Santa Clarita, a suburb north of Los Angeles, where I attended <a href="https://www.sauguscenturions.com/">Saugus High School</a> from
		2018 to 2022, graduating as salutatorian with a 4.79 GPA and 1520 SAT score (800 math, 720 English). I  
		attended <a href="https://www.ucsb.edu/">UC Santa Barbara</a> from 2022 to 2026, majoring in computer science, where I participated in 
		the <a href="https://ersp.cs.ucsb.edu/">Early Research Scholars Program</a> during my 3rd year, and graduated with a 3.64 GPA and honors.
		I currently work as a software engineer for Santa Barbara-based company <a href="https://umbra.space/">Umbra Space</a>, which manufactures
		satellites that use synthetic aperture radar to image the Earth at high resolution.
		</p>
		<p>
		In addition to software engineering, I am interested in geography, physics, math, and astronomy. I am interested in making maps - I drafted a
		congressional district map of California following the 2020 census, and have made several maps of the world and the United States using QGIS
		and Inkscape, including demographic, electoral, weather/climate, and topographic maps.
		</p>
		</section>

		<style>
			section ul {
				list-style: disc;
				padding-left: 1.5rem;
			}
		</style>

		<section>
			<h2>Links</h2>
			<ul>
				<li><a href="https://www.linkedin.com/in/sanjayksrikanth/">LinkedIn</a></li>
				<li><a href="https://github.com/crosscountrycoder">GitHub</a></li>
				<li><a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/User:Crossover1370">Wikipedia user page</a></li>
				<li><a href="http://reddit.com/user/crosscountrycoder">Reddit</a></li>
			</ul>
		</section>
		<section>
			<h2>Projects</h2>
			<ul>
				<li><a href="#">Coming soon</a></li>
			</ul>
		</section>

		<section>
			<h2>Calculators</h2>
			<ul>
				<li><a href="/calculators">View all calculators</a></li>
			</ul>
		</section>
	</main>
</Layout>

<script>
	const birthdate = new Date('2003-12-19');
	const now = new Date();
	let age = now.getFullYear() - birthdate.getFullYear();
	if (
		now.getMonth() < birthdate.getMonth() ||
		(now.getMonth() === birthdate.getMonth() && now.getDate() < birthdate.getDate())
	) {
		age--;
	}
	document.getElementById('age')!.textContent = String(age);
</script>
